Subject: Re: [T2] Throttle Cable - Guide Tube Through Fan Housing

> This is for a 71 bus, stock 1600 CC type 1 dual port engine.  The short
> (about
> 4 inches long, or so) tube that goes through the fan housing and guides
> the
> throttle cable from the point where it exits the bus body, to the throttle
> arm
> on the carburetor, keeps sliding out of the fan housing,

You can put a small hose clamp on the tube at the back of the housing if
you don't have Popeye forearms and can do it by feel alone. Otherwise you
have to pull the engine to see what's what.
